#: ../../../advanced/pipeline.rst:48
msgid ""
"In order to understand better how the pipeline mode works, we should take a "
"closer look at the `PostgreSQL client-server message flow`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/pipeline.rst:51
msgid ""
"During normal querying, each statement is transmitted by the client to the "
"server as a stream of request messages, terminating with a **Sync** message "
"to tell it that it should process the messages sent so far. The server will "
"execute the statement and describe the results back as a stream of messages, "
"terminating with a **ReadyForQuery**, telling the client that it may now "
"send a new query."
msgstr ""

